		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="bfont"> From: Job</font><BR><font class="bfont"><A HREF='/lotr/main/spoilers.php'>Back to Spoilers List</A></font><TABLE WIDTH=100% border="0" cellpadding="6"><tr><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="h2font"> Name</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="h2font"> Comment</td></tr><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>dive</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">the new legolas is actually good: play 2 thors maps to make sure you can play your forest or river, then play a bow for arwen and aragors bow, splendor of their banners and 2 double shots (no more, you don&#39;t want them to stack into your hand)AND play gondor&#39;s bowmen!!!this card is awesome: it&#39;s a free condition that lets you add 2 to the archery total anytime you want to sac it (drawback: exert a man), so it does not stays in your hand (therefor it&#39;s so much better then double shot) and it&#39;s not unique. so when necessary, you can have more then 10 archery total at any site.<br>
<br>
also check out long knives of legolas! a very good card (decipher&#39;s site) that suits better on the new legolas then on greenleaf<br>
<br>
greenleaf still rules, but i think the new lelolas is very good too in the right deck </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont"><B>jesus</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont">new legolas has potential.  i play with greenleaf and against him more often then not.  he is a hafling.  90% of the time he is exhausted so he can&#39;t fight.  this new one is a figher, even more then prince but the new one adds to the archery and that always helps.  then you can actually use the bow of the galadrahim and wound minions (i.e. arv and the cave troll and a runner live after archery.  cave troll dies bioch.  double shot is crap, splendor is somewhat usefull if you are goin hardcore un aimed archery, or the white arrows to get some cards out of their hands.<br>
but thats just my take on it </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Discard</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">I think the new Lego would work well in a discard deck. Healed by Aragorn, and can exert for White Arrows instead of directed archery. </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont"><B>Amrou Kithikin</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#A2B1C1><font class="bfont">Double shot is a good card, if used well.  And the new legolas is not anywhere near as good as Greenleaf, but he&#39;s much better than the prince of mirkwood.   </TD></TR><TR><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>Turambar</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">My sentiments exactly. I have experimented with unaimed archery and it gets the job done. 5+ archery a turn means unless your opponent can get out enough minions, you&#39;re basically getting a free ride. Or even if you can&#39;t, a key exertion from Aragorn or the archer allies will leave your opponent in a dire state of mind: Play minions now and let them be futile or play later together and clog my hand? The reason it&#39;s &#39;crap&#39; now is because aimed archery is the rage currently and is more consistent in getting the job done in tournaments and such, and thus leaves no room for people to even take a second glance at unaimed archery. These cards can definitely balance the former. Those KiE-Son of Thranduil-Splendor of Their Banners are certainly very workable and feasible combos which aren&#39;t hard to set up, and shouldn&#39;t be scoffed at.<br>
<br>
